'''Cliff Birch''' (born 1 September 1928, [[Newport]], [[Monmouthshire (historic)|Monmouthshire]], died 1990) was a Welsh professional footballer. A right-wing, he began his career with Ebbw Vale and joined [[Norwich City F.C.|Norwich]] in 1949. In 1950 he joined [[Newport County A.F.C.|Newport County]] and made 142 [[Football League]] appearances for the club, scoring 28 goals. In 1954 he moved to Colchester United and later to Spalding United <ref>[http://www.neilbrown.newcastlefans.com/newport/newport.htm Newport County A-Z of transfers]</ref>.

